ions":["$\\mathrm{RbCl}$","$\\mathrm{NaCl}$","$\\mathrm{CsCl}$","$\\mathrm{LiCl}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{RbCl}, \\mathrm{NaCl}$ and $\\mathrm{CsCl}$ share the same crystal structure except $\\mathrm{LiCl}$.\n$\\mathrm{LiCl}$ is deliquescent. It crystalises as a hydrated LiCl. $2 \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}$. Other alkali metal chlorides do not form hydrates.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":31616,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["Covalent solid","Molecular solid","Ionic solid","Network solid"],"answer":1,"solution":"Molecular solid is the best description of water in the solid phase. For example ice is hydrogen bonded molecular solid.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null}]